files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.AddTexturePostProcess
files.Summary: A post process that overlays a texture on top of the scene, respecting transparency. See ../common/docs/effects-reference-common.html#add-texture.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.AdjustGammaPostProcess
files.Summary: A post process that adjust the gamma of the image. See ../common/docs/effects-reference-common.html#adjust-gamma.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.BilateralFilterPostProcess
files.Summary: A post process that smooths the image using an edge-preserving, noise-reducing filter. See ../common/docs/effects-reference-common.html#bilateral-filter.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.BlendTexturePostProcess
files.Summary: A post process that outputs a fullscreen constant textureTiling. See ../common/docs/effects-reference-common.html#blend-texture.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.BoxBlurPostProcess
files.Summary: A post process that applies a uniform blur by averaging neighbor pixels colors. See ../common/docs/effects-reference-common.html#box-blur.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.ConvexHullMapPostProcess
files.Summary: A post process that gradually shifts colors toward the provided primaries, producing posterized, clustered, or paletteconstrained looks. See ../common/docs/effects-reference-common.html#convex-hull-map.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.DesaturatePostProcess
files.Summary: A post process to see the image's luminosity. See ../common/docs/effects-reference-common.html#desaturate.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.GaussianBlurPostProcess
files.Summary: A post process that applies a smooth, natural-looking blur using a Gaussian weight curve. See ../common/docs/effects-reference-common.html#gaussian-blur.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.MaxPostProcess
files.Summary: A post process that replaces each pixel with the maximum color value found in its neighborhood. See ../common/docs/effects-reference-common.html#max-filter.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.MinPostProcess
files.Summary: A post process that replaces each pixel with the minimum color value found in its neighborhood. See ../common/docs/effects-reference-common.html#min-filter.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.MixboxConvexHullMapPostProcess
files.Summary: A post process that pushes each pixels color toward chosen primaries using convex-hull projection, but blends them with Mixbox for more natural, smoother color transitions than normal interpolation. See ../common/docs/effects-reference-common.html#mixbox-convex-hull-map.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.PixelatePostProcess
files.Summary: A post process that applies a pixelation effect to the image by sampling blocks of pixels instead of individual texels. See ../common/docs/effects-reference-common.html#pixelate.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.PowerMeanPostProcess
files.Summary: A post process that blurs the image by computing a power mean (p-norm mean) of neighboring pixels. See ../common/docs/effects-reference-common.html#power-mean.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.QuantizePostProcess
files.Summary: A post process that reduces the number of distinct color values in the image, creating a posterized or stylized effect. See ../common/docs/effects-reference-common.html#quantize.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.TriToneMapPostProcess
files.Summary: Maps the images tones to three colors (low, mid, and high) based on lightness, smoothly blending between them using inverse linear interpolation. See ../common/docs/effects-reference-common.html#tri-tone-map.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.GenericPostProcess
files.Summary: Allows you to use an arbitrary shader as a full screen post process effect and configure its properties in the inspector.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.IPostProcess
files.Summary: Interface for post process effects.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.NamedShaderPostProcess
files.Summary: A post process shader that gets the shader to use from the name.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.PostProcess
files.Summary: Contains basic functionality for a full screen post process effect.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.PostProcessRunner
files.Summary: Runs all post-processes found in children of a given root on the this script is attached to.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.SeparableNamedShaderPostProcess
files.Summary: Encapsulates a post process based on a separable filter, such as a box blur.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.CrossHatching.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.ConvexHullHatchPostProcess
files.Summary: A post-process that maps each pixel's color toward a set of primary colors but modulates the projection with a hatching texture. See ../cross-hatching/docs/effects-reference-crosshatching.html#convex-hull-hatch

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.CrossHatching.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.SimpleHatchPostProcess
files.Summary: A post-process that adds layered cross-hatching based on brightness: dark areas get more rotated hatch layers, while bright areas stay mostly clear. See ../cross-hatching/docs/effects-reference-crosshatching.html#simple-hatch

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.CrossHatching.OrientationScheme
files.Summary: Schemes for orienting hatch layers.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.CrossHatching.URP.PostProcessing.Effects.GLConvexHullHatchRenderFeature
files.Summary: A post-process that maps each pixel's color toward a set of primary colors but modulates the projection with a hatching texture.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.CrossHatching.URP.PostProcessing.Effects.GLMixboxConvexHullHatchRenderFeature
files.Summary: A post-process that uses a hatching texture to project colors through a convex-hull palette, then blends them with Mixbox for more natural, ink-like color mixing. See ../cross-hatching/docs/effects-reference-crosshatching.html#mixbox-convex-hull-hatch

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.CrossHatching.URP.PostProcessing.Effects.GLMixboxConvexHullMapRenderFeature
files.Summary: A post process that pushes each pixels color toward chosen primaries using convex-hull projection, but blends them with Mixbox for more natural, smoother color transitions than normal interpolation. See ../common/docs/effects-reference-common.html#mixbox-convex-hull-map.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.CrossHatching.URP.PostProcessing.Effects.GLSimpleHatchRenderFeature
files.Summary: A post-process that adds layered cross-hatching based on brightness: dark areas get more rotated hatch layers, while bright areas stay mostly clear. See ../cross-hatching/docs/effects-reference-crosshatching.html#simple-hatch

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.Dithering.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.DitherMatrixBiasPostProcess
files.Summary: A post process that applies a data-driven dither matrix. See ../dithering/docs/effects-reference-dithering.html#dither-matrix-bias

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.Dithering.BuiltIn.PostProcessing.Effects.DitherTextureBiasPostProcess
files.Summary: Post process effect that applies quantization with a dither texture bias pattern. See ../dithering/docs/effects-reference-dithering.html#dither-texture-bias

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.Dithering.DitherMatrixPresets
files.Summary: Contains preset dither matrices.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.Dithering.Editor.DitherPatternGenerator
files.Summary: Editor window that generates textures based on a FloatMatrix pattern.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.Dithering.URP.GLDitherMatrixBiasRenderFeature
files.Summary: A post process that applies a data-driven dither matrix. See ../dithering/docs/effects-reference-dithering.html#dither-matrix-bias

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.Dithering.URP.GLDitherTextureBiasRenderFeature
files.Summary: Post process effect that applies quantization with a dither texture bias pattern. See ../dithering/docs/effects-reference-dithering.html#dither-texture-bias

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.Editor.TextureGenerator.ColorList
files.Summary: Wraps a list of colors in a .

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.Editor.TextureGenerator.GradientTextureGenerator
files.Summary: Editor window for generating gradient textures.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.Editor.TextureGenerator.PatternTextureGenerator
files.Summary: Editor window for generating checkerboard textures.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.Editor.TextureGenerator.TextureGeneratorWindow
files.Summary: A window that can be used as a base class for texture generation windows. See the code of for an example of how to implement a texture generation window.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.EditorTextureGenerator.PropertyNotfoundException
files.Summary: Thrown when looking for a property (for example, in a serialized object) and the property is not found.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.EditorTextureGenerator.SerializedPropertyExtensions
files.Summary: Provides extension methods for .

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.FloatMatrix
files.Summary: A serializable data-driven dither matrix. Stores an array of normalized float values along with matrix dimensions.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.Keyword
files.Summary: Represents a shader keyword, and whether it is present ot not.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.KeywordSet
files.Summary: Represents a set of mutually exclusive keywords of a shader.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.MaterialExtensions
files.Summary: Provides extension methods for configuring materials used by Gamelogic Fx effects. These helpers simplify setting keyword collections, texture tiling, color lists, and kernel parameters in a consistent and centralized way.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.MatrixArray
files.Summary: Represents a two-dimensional matrix stored internally as a flat float array. The matrix layout and interpretation are controlled by the field.

files.Title: Gamelogic.Fx.RequiresMixboxAttribute
files.Summary: Used to flag components that needs Mixbox to work.
